{"relationshipsSections":[{"identifiers":["doc:\/\/GIO\/4GLib14PointerWrapperP","doc:\/\/GIO\/10GLibObject14GWeakCapturingP","doc:\/\/GIO\/10GLibObject0B8ProtocolP","doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/MenuModelProtocol"],"title":"Conforms To","type":"conformsTo","kind":"relationships"}],"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"declarations","declarations":[{"languages":["swift"],"tokens":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"struct"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"text":"MenuModelRef","kind":"identifier"}],"platforms":["macOS"]}]},{"content":[{"level":2,"text":"Overview","type":"heading","anchor":"overview"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"The conceptual model of menus in ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GMenuModel"},{"text":" is hierarchical:","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"sections and submenus are again represented by "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GMenuModel"},{"text":"s.","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"Menus themselves do not define their own roles. Rather, the role"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"of a particular "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GMenuModel"},{"text":" is defined by the item that references","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"it (or, in the case of the ‘root’ menu, is defined by the context"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"in which it is used).","type":"text"}]},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"As an example, consider the visible portions of this menu:"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"level":2,"type":"heading","text":"An example menu","anchor":"An-example-menu"},{"inlineContent":[],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"While this kind of deeply nested menu is no longer considered good UI"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"practice, it serves as a good example of the concepts in "},{"code":"GMenuModel","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":".","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"There are 8 ‘menus’ visible in the screenshot: one menubar, two","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"submenus and 5 sections:","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"the toplevel menubar (containing 4 items)","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"the View submenu (containing 3 sections)"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"the first section of the View submenu (containing 2 items)","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"the second section of the View submenu (containing 1 item)"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"the final section of the View submenu (containing 1 item)","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"the Highlight Mode submenu (containing 2 sections)"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"the Sources section (containing 2 items)","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"the Markup section (containing 2 items)"}]}]}],"type":"unorderedList"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"The ","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"#a-menu-example"},{"text":" illustrates the conceptual connection between","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"these 8 menus. Each large block in the figure represents a menu and the"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"smaller blocks within the large block represent items in that menu. Some"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"items contain references to other menus."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"heading","anchor":"A-menu-example","text":"A menu example","level":2},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Notice that the separators visible in the ","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","identifier":"#an-example-menu","isActive":true},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"appear nowhere in the "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"#a-menu-example","overridingTitle":"menu model","overridingTitleInlineContent":[{"text":"menu model","type":"text"}]},{"type":"text","text":". This is because"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"separators are not explicitly represented in the menu model. Instead,","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"a separator is inserted between any two non-empty sections of a menu.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"Section items can have labels just like any other item. In that case,","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"a display system may show a section header instead of a separator."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The motivation for this abstract model of application controls is"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"that modern user interfaces tend to make these controls available","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"outside the application. Examples include global menus, jumplists,","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"dash boards, etc. To support such uses, it is necessary to ‘export’"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"information about actions and their representation in menus, which"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"is exactly what the action group exporter and the menu model exporter do for","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"[iface"},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/ActionGroup"},{"text":"] and [class","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/MenuModel","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":"]. The client-side"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"counterparts to make use of the exported information are","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"[class"},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/DBusActionGroup"},{"type":"text","text":"] and [class"},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/DBusMenuModel"},{"text":"].","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The API of "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GMenuModel"},{"text":" is very generic, with iterators for the","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"attributes and links of an item, see"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"[method","type":"text"},{"code":"Gio.MenuModel.iterate_item_attributes","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":"] and","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"[method","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Gio.MenuModel.iterate_item_links"},{"type":"text","text":"]. The ‘standard’ attributes and"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"link types have predefined names: "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"G_MENU_ATTRIBUTE_LABEL"},{"type":"text","text":","},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"G_MENU_ATTRIBUTE_ACTION"},{"type":"text","text":", "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"G_MENU_ATTRIBUTE_TARGET"},{"type":"text","text":", "},{"code":"G_MENU_LINK_SECTION","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"and "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"G_MENU_LINK_SUBMENU"},{"text":".","type":"text"}]},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Items in a ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GMenuModel"},{"type":"text","text":" represent active controls if they refer to"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"an action that can get activated when the user interacts with the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"menu item. The reference to the action is encoded by the string ID"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"in the "},{"code":"G_MENU_ATTRIBUTE_ACTION","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" attribute. An action ID uniquely"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"identifies an action in an action group. Which action "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"group(s)"},{"type":"text","text":" provide"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"actions depends on the context in which the menu model is used."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"E.g. when the model is exported as the application menu of a","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"identifier":"https:\/\/docs.gtk.org\/gtk4\/class.Application.html","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":","},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"actions can be application-wide or window-specific (and thus come from"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"two different action groups). By convention, the application-wide actions","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"have names that start with "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"app."},{"text":", while the names of window-specific","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"actions start with "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"win."},{"text":".","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"While a wide variety of stateful actions is possible, the following"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"is the minimum that is expected to be supported by all users of exported"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"menu information:","type":"text"}]},{"type":"unorderedList","items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"an action with no parameter type and no state","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"an action with no parameter type and boolean state"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"an action with string parameter type and string state"}]}]}]},{"level":2,"type":"heading","anchor":"Stateless","text":"Stateless"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"A stateless action typically corresponds to an ordinary menu item."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Selecting such a menu item will activate the action (with no parameter)."}]},{"level":2,"type":"heading","text":"Boolean State","anchor":"Boolean-State"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"An action with a boolean state will most typically be used with a ‘toggle’"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"or ‘switch’ menu item. The state can be set directly, but activating the","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"action (with no parameter) results in the state being toggled."}]},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Selecting a toggle menu item will activate the action. The menu item should","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"be rendered as ‘checked’ when the state is true."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"text":"String Parameter and State","level":2,"type":"heading","anchor":"String-Parameter-and-State"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Actions with string parameters and state will most typically be used to","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"represent an enumerated choice over the items available for a group of"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"radio menu items. Activating the action with a string parameter is","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"equivalent to setting that parameter as the state."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Radio menu items, in addition to being associated with the action, will"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"have a target value. Selecting that menu item will result in activation"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"of the action with the target value as the parameter. The menu item should"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"be rendered as ‘selected’ when the state of the action is equal to the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"target value of the menu item.","type":"text"}]},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/MenuModelRef","isActive":true},{"text":" type acts as a lightweight Swift reference to an underlying ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GMenuModel"},{"text":" instance.","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"It exposes methods that can operate on this data type through ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/MenuModelProtocol","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"text":" conformance.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"Use "},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/MenuModelRef","type":"reference"},{"text":" only as an ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"unowned"},{"type":"text","text":" reference to an existing "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GMenuModel"},{"text":" instance.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"aside","name":"Note","content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Use ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/MenuModel","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"text":" (instead of ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/MenuModelRef","type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":") if you want to use Automatic Reference Counting for memory management of the underlying "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GMenuModel"},{"text":" instance.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}],"style":"note"}],"kind":"content"}],"variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}],"paths":["\/documentation\/gio\/menumodelref"]}],"abstract":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GMenuModel"},{"type":"text","text":" represents the contents of a menu — an ordered list of"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"menu items. The items are associated with actions, which can be"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"activated through them. Items can be grouped in sections, and may","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"have submenus associated with them. Both items and sections usually"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"have some representation data, such as labels or icons. The type of"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"the associated action (ie whether it is stateful, and what kind of"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"state it has) can influence the representation of the item."}],"schemaVersion":{"minor":3,"patch":0,"major":0},"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO"]]},"identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/MenuModelRef","interfaceLanguage":"swift"},"kind":"symbol","metadata":{"modules":[{"name":"GIO"}],"navigatorTitle":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"MenuModelRef"}],"externalID":"s:3GIO12MenuModelRefV","roleHeading":"Structure","symbolKind":"struct","role":"symbol","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"struct"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"MenuModelRef","kind":"identifier"}],"title":"MenuModelRef"},"topicSections":[{"identifiers":["doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/MenuModelRef\/init(_:)-349jz","doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/MenuModelRef\/init(_:)-36vr0","doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/MenuModelRef\/init(_:)-41da1","doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/MenuModelRef\/init(_:)-669zx","doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/MenuModelRef\/init(_:)-8pdws","doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/MenuModelRef\/init(cPointer:)","doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/MenuModelRef\/init(constPointer:)","doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/MenuModelRef\/init(gconstpointer:)","doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/MenuModelRef\/init(gpointer:)","doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/MenuModelRef\/init(mutating:)","doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/MenuModelRef\/init(opaquePointer:)"],"title":"Initializers","generated":true,"anchor":"Initializers"},{"identifiers":["doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/MenuModelRef\/ptr"],"anchor":"Instance-Properties","title":"Instance Properties","generated":true},{"title":"Type Methods","anchor":"Type-Methods","identifiers":["doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/MenuModelRef\/unowned(_:)"],"generated":true},{"anchor":"Default-Implementations","generated":true,"title":"Default Implementations","identifiers":["doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/MenuModelRef\/GWeakCapturing-Implementations","doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/MenuModelRef\/MenuModelProtocol-Implementations","doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/MenuModelRef\/ObjectProtocol-Implementations"]}],"sections":[],"references":{"doc://GIO/documentation/GIO/MenuModel":{"type":"topic","navigatorTitle":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"MenuModel"}],"kind":"symbol","role":"symbol","identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/MenuModel","url":"\/documentation\/gio\/menumodel","title":"MenuModel","fragments":[{"text":"class","kind":"keyword"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"text":"MenuModel","kind":"identifier"}],"abstract":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GMenuModel"},{"type":"text","text":" represents the contents of a menu — an ordered list of"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"menu items. The items are associated with actions, which can be","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"activated through them. Items can be grouped in sections, and may","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"have submenus associated with them. Both items and sections usually","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"have some representation data, such as labels or icons. The type of"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"the associated action (ie whether it is stateful, and what kind of"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"state it has) can influence the representation of the item."}]},"#a-menu-example":{"type":"link","title":"example","titleInlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"example"}],"url